30/11/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Jadranka Kosor announced on Saturday (November 28th) that 273m euros from the 2010 budget will be earmarked for activities and projects related to EU membership.
Most will go to adjustments in the agriculture sector.
Croatia will also spend money to bring border security in line with Schengen criteria and on judicial reform.
Croatia hopes to wrap up its EU accession talks by mid-2010.
(AFP, Poslovni, HINA - 28/11/09)
